            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Hello @motine,\n\n`app.run` passes the `ssl_context` argument to `werkzeug.serving.run_simple`. And in fact it is described in Werkzeug's documentation: http://werkzeug.pocoo.org/docs/serving/#quickstart\n\nSo what you have to do is to pass a tuple of the form `('/path/to/the/key.crt', '/path/to/the/key.key')` instead of the string `\"adhoc\"`.\n\nAs a side note, the issue tracker is usually not the appropriate place to ask usage-related questions. It doesn't help that GitHub calls it \"issues\" while it's usually called a \"bug tracker\", and that there are currently relatively little ways available (StackOverflow and the `#pocoo` channel on freenode) for asking a question about Flask _with the chance of getting a response_.\n"
        },
