            "body": "Oh. Indeed i didn't seem to read your question at all, sorry.\n\nI can't think of a way to do this with the builtin server and without patching the code. So i think the best you can do in development is to just use nginx in dev too. Actually that doesn't seem like such a bad move, you could configure nginx in upstart, systemd or whatever to start as part of the boot process. Then you start the development server at any time on the port you configured nginx to proxy to.\n"
